Request 3 by Gracierocket
Northanger Abbey - Jane Austen 
Catherine Morland, Henry Tilney

So, although I love Henry, I've always found something just a shade troubling in his relationship with Catherine. He occasionally makes jokes that go over her head, and doesn't feel the need to include her in them, and he has so much more knowledge and experience that their relationship seemed a little unbalanced. 

I ship it, because he's funny and smart and warm, and their love for each other is absolutely sincere, but I'd like to see what their relationship looks like when Catherine has had chance to grow up a bit, and their marriage is a little more equal. I reckon it would be a great marriage about ten years down the line - I think Henry would slip from affection to affectionate respect very easily.

So! Maybe a fun, faux-gothic adventure where the two of them, now an established married couple, get to go and uncover a mystery together? We get to see how their dynamic works when it's a bit more balanced, but still just as fun and loving? We get to see the woman Catherine grows up to be?


